You can add your voice to the tens of thousands of comments posted daily on Express.co.uk and have your say on the big issues facing the country today. Conservative Party leaders are yet to announce a concrete timetable for Mr Johnson's replacement, but a candidate roster is emerging. So far, four have come forward, with an already diverse selection of personalities and policies emerging from the Prime Minister's political demise. Suella Braverman emerged first before he resigned on Thursday, followed by Tom Tugendhat, Rishi Sunak and Kemi Badenoch. Brexit is one of the prime concerns for prospective voters, with every candidate so far committed to carrying on the process. But ultimately, MPs and Tory members - who represent 0.39 percent of the UK - will get their say as to who becomes the next Prime Minister. Other Britons will have to wait until a General Election, so, as they wait, they can endorse their favourite candidates in the comments below. HAVE YOUR SAY RIGHT NOW - JOIN THE EXPRESS READER DEBATE IN OUR COMMENTS SECTION.